						               													<description>After centuries of fighting, the ninja clans have merged into one, but for the new clan to work, they must be able to coordinate their training together.&amp;#10;Play as masters and organize ninja movements and attacks.&amp;#10;The future of the new clan is in your hands!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this game each player acts as a ninja master and must face a board of 3x3 cards.&amp;#10;The goal in this game is to line up three ninjas with the same posture (4 types: pose, kick, smoke bomb, attack), either forming a row or a column. The color of the ninja does not matter to make these trios.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During their turn, each player can do one of these three actions:&amp;#10;1. Flip a card to reveal which kind of ninja or hidden action contain.&amp;#10;2. Swap two orthogonally adjacent cards.&amp;#10;3. Discard one of the 9 cards in exchange of a random card from the top of the game deck (training deck).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a player lines up three ninjas with the same pose, the master must say the words &amp;quot;Nin-Nin&amp;quot;. The master now can take and reserve the three ninjas to one side of the table (to count points at the end of the game), taking three new unrevealed cards from the training deck and turning over an already revealed card to each other players (masters).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game will be over when the cards in the game deck are gone, and a master with all the cards revealed can no longer make any ninja trios. The player with the most ninja points will be the winner of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
